Reasoning: The paper focuses on the role of stochastic gradient descent (SGD) implicit regularization in deep learning systems for natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the generalization performance of over-parameterized models, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of neural networks in NLP tasks suggests the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions decision boundary visualization, which is a common technique in computer vision, falling under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of limited training samples and corrupted labels, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
